<article>
    <div class="title" id="article-or-section-and-aside">
        <h2>Article or Section</h2>
        <h4>> HTML</h4>
    </div>

    <p>A <em>section</em> is used to group different <em>articles</em> into different
        purposes or subjects, or to define the different sections of a single <em>article</em>.</p>

    {{{ startCode lang="html" text="Example:"}}}
        <section id="content">
            <article>
                <h2>Hello, I'm a article</h2>
                <p>and I'm inside a section</p>
            </article>
            <article>
                <h2>Hello, I'm a another article</h2>
                <p>Look at me!</p>
            </article>
        </section>
    {{{ endCode }}}

    <img src="imgs/article-or-section.png" alt="An example of section and article"></img>

    <p>The <em>aside</em> tag shows content related to parent content. For example a
        a quotation inside a article</p>

    {{{ startCode lang="html" text="Example:"}}}
            <article>
                <h2>Hello, I'm a article</h2>
                <p>and I'm inside a section</p>
                <aside>
                    <h4>From Iron Man</h4>
                    <p>2018</p>
                </aside>
            </article>
    {{{ endCode }}}

    <section class="source">
        Source:
        <ol>
            <li><a href="https://stackoverflow.com/a/24764861">https://stackoverflow.com/a/24764861</a></li>
        </ol>
    </section>
</article>
